comments: Johnson (SAS) brings his hand down and makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) arm that affects his put back at the rim.
Johnson (SAS) makes clean ball contact to dislodge the rebound away from Jokic (DEN).
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) briefly grasps and immediately releases Poeltl's (SAS) uniform as the pick is set.
Jokic (DEN) is moving alongside Vassell's (SAS) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Johnson (SAS) contests the floating shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Jokic's (DEN) arm after the release.
Jokic (DEN) cleanly deflects the ball away from Poeltl (SAS) during rebounding.
Richardson (SAS) cleanly deflects the pass and is able to save the ball from going out of bounds before he steps on the baseline.
Jones (SAS) and Brown (DEN) come together at the same spot and marginal contact occurs as they pursue the loose ball.
Vassell (SAS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Brown (DEN) during rebounding.  Any follow-through arm contact after the ball is dislodged is deemed incidental.
Richardson (SAS) is the last player to touch the ball before it goes out of bounds. Possession is correctly retained by the Nuggets.
Jones (SAS) and Murray (DEN) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs during the inbounds.
Brown (DEN) establishes himself in Poeltl's (SAS) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Poeltl (SAS) is already in Murray's (DEN) path and is firming up over his right leg when marginal contact occurs.
Poeltl (SAS) establishes himself in Murray's (DEN) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) cleanly deflects the ball away from Richardson (SAS) during his drive.  Any ensuing foot to ball contact after the deflection is considered incidental.
Poeltl (SAS) brings his arm toward Murray's (DEN) path and marginal contact occurs during Murray's drive.
Brown (DEN) legally contests Vassell's (SAS) jump shot attempt.
Johnson (SAS) briefly rests a hand on Jokic's (DEN) chest and marginal contact occurs as he starts his dribble up the court.
Johnson (SAS) reaches in and makes contact with Jokic's (DEN) body, which affects his SQBR as he brings the ball up the court.
During the inbound, Jones (SAS) and Murray (DEN) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
McDermott (SAS) is in the paint for less than three seconds when he is imminently exiting.
Jones (SAS) makes clean contact with the ball on his tie up attempt with Murray (DEN). The Denver bench is awarded a timeout simultaneous to the start of the tie up.
During the inbound, Sochan (SAS) and Jokic (DEN) mutually engage and disengage with one another and marginal contact occurs off-ball.
Sochan (SAS) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs with Jokic's (DEN) arm, which does not affect his ability to maintain full control and make his intended pass.
